result.execSummary:
The defendant Chandler C Eaton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Chandler C Eaton is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Chandler C Eaton was found guilty of Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Maintain full-time employment/education or combination of or be seeking same, and treatment.

Defendant shall not use/possess drug paraphernalia and/or controlled substances without a valid prescription.  Defendant shall not have any contact, direct or indirect, with PB or JB. Not to possess any ID information or documents not in def's name. Def has curfew of 6 pm to 6 am for first 6 mo of probation.
Court finds defendant eligible for expunction under 973.015 if successful completion of probation.

Random UA & BA testing at discretion of agent.  Pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.  Defendant advised of requirement to provide DNA sample.  Any other conditions DOC, Probation/Parole Department may impose.

timeConds.notes: With huber. Consec to 14CF1166. Credit does NOT apply.

supervisions.notes: Concur to 14CF1931 but consec to 16CF1332. Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

superMiscConds.notes: Defendant advised of requirement to provide DNA sample-on file.  Defendant shall complete a risk and needs assessment and comply with care plan goals related to prioritized need areas identified.  Any other conditions DOC, Probation/Parole Department may impose.
